    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<h3 id=\"SolarisLimitations-KnownLimitations\">Known Limitations</h3><h4 id=\"SolarisLimitations-Geometry\">Geometry</h4><ul><li><p>NURBS and Implicits not supported</p></li></ul><h4 id=\"SolarisLimitations-Shading\">Shading</h4><ul><li><p>For best performance, you should manually pre-convert your textures via <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/REN26/pages/19661963/txmake\" data-linked-resource-id=\"19661963\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">txmake</a> or use the Texture Manager</p></li><li><p>The dynamic and uniform array node is not expected to work in Solaris</p></li></ul><h4 id=\"SolarisLimitations-ImageTool\">Image Tool</h4><ul><li><p>Rendering to IT with ACES currently needs the env variable <strong>IT_OCIOV1 </strong>to be set to your ACES config.ocio</p></li><li><p>Crop tool and image selector is not supported</p></li></ul><h4 id=\"SolarisLimitations-OSX\"><strong>OSX</strong></h4><ul><li><p>M1 on OSX is not currently supported.  <br/>You can run via Rosetta, but be warned, performance won't be as good until native support is added.</p></li></ul>"
    }
  },
